The paper deals with the Restricted Isometry Property (RIP) and its application in Johnson-Lindenstrauss embeddings, which are commonly studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions compressed sensing (cs.DS), which is closely related to RIP. Additionally, the paper involves matrix theory and optimization, which are relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI).
